Class SynchronizedFloatObjectMap<V>

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.collections.impl.map.mutable.primitive.SynchronizedFloatObjectMap<V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Iterable<V>, InternalIterable<V>, FloatObjectMap<V>, MutableFloatObjectMap<V>, MutablePrimitiveObjectMap<V>, PrimitiveObjectMap<V>, RichIterable<V>
public class SynchronizedFloatObjectMap<V> extends Object implements MutableFloatObjectMap<V>, Serializable
A synchronized view of a MutableFloatObjectMap. It is imperative that the user manually synchronize on the collection when iterating over it using the standard JDK iterator or JDK 5 for loop, as per Collections.synchronizedCollection(Collection).
